Tmux Tricks

To copy from clipboard into tmux : Ctrl Shift v

To open tmux : type tmux
to name a session : tmux new -s session_name
to detach from the tmux session : Ctrl,b d
to list all currently  running session : tmux ls

To attach to a session : tmux attach-session -t 0

Working with Tmux windows and Panes

To create a new window with shell : Ctrl,b c

to choose window from list : Ctrl b,w
to switch to windows by number : Ctrl b, N(number)
to rename current window  :Ctrl b ,
to split current pane into two panes horizontally : Ctrl b, %
To close current pane  : Ctrl b, x
to toggle between the current and previous pane : Ctrl b , ;
to split vertically into two panes : Ctrl b, "

Customizing Tmux
you tinker with this file to customise tmux :  ~/.tmux.conf

Basic TMux usage:
create session : tmux new -s session_name
run program
detach for session: Ctrl b, d
reattach to session : tmux attach-session -t session_name

My_tmux_Mappings
c-space  :prefix
prefix, hjkl for navigation between panes
prefix, :
prefix, v for vertical split
prefix, d for horizontal split

prefix + zoom out
prefix - zoom in 

